00:02:02.031 --> 00:02:05.090
Richard Thaler is renowned
for his influential

00:02:05.090 --> 00:02:07.083
contributions over the last three decades

00:02:07.083 --> 00:02:10.781
to the emerging field
of behavioral economics.

00:02:10.781 --> 00:02:14.390
He is considered by many to be the pioneer

00:02:14.390 --> 00:02:16.850
in integrating psychological research

00:02:16.850 --> 00:02:19.057
with economic theory and the inventor

00:02:19.057 --> 00:02:23.680
of the field of behavioral economics.

00:02:23.680 --> 00:02:26.930
Thaler's studies also
focus on behavioral finance

00:02:26.930 --> 00:02:29.870
and the psychology of decision making.

00:02:29.870 --> 00:02:31.710
He explores the implications of loosening

00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:34.173
the standard economic
assumption that everyone

00:02:34.173 --> 00:02:37.610
in the economy is rational and selfish.

00:02:37.610 --> 00:02:39.838
Instead considering the
possibility that some

00:02:39.838 --> 00:02:44.276
of the participants in the
economy are sometimes human.

00:02:44.276 --> 00:02:47.033
Thaler received his BA from
Case Western Reserve University

00:02:47.033 --> 00:02:50.317
in 1967 and his MA and PhD

00:02:50.317 --> 00:02:53.080
from the University of Rochester in 1970

00:02:53.080 --> 00:02:55.430
and '74 respectively.

00:02:55.430 --> 00:02:58.400
Between 1974 and 1980,
he held the positions

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:00.700
of assistant professor
at the graduate school

00:03:00.700 --> 00:03:02.914
of management of the
University of Rochester.

00:03:02.914 --> 00:03:04.790
And assistant professor of economics

00:03:04.790 --> 00:03:06.721
and public administration at the graduate

00:03:06.721 --> 00:03:09.240
School of Business and
Public Administration

00:03:09.240 --> 00:03:11.340
at Cornell University.

00:03:11.340 --> 00:03:13.944
From 1980 to 1988 he was
professor of economics

00:03:13.944 --> 00:03:17.765
at Cornell's Johnson Graduate
School of Management.

00:03:17.765 --> 00:03:20.150
He is currently the Robert P. Gwen

00:03:20.150 --> 00:03:22.782
Professor of Behavioral
Science and Economics,

00:03:22.782 --> 00:03:26.310
as well as director of the
Center of Decision Research

00:03:26.310 --> 00:03:29.238
at the University of Chicago,
Graduate School of Business,

00:03:29.238 --> 00:03:31.710
where he has help appointments since 1995.

00:03:35.381 --> 00:03:37.660
Thaler is also a research associate

00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:39.349
at the National Bureau
of Economic Research,

00:03:39.349 --> 00:03:43.050
where he co-directs the
behavioral economics project.

00:03:43.050 --> 00:03:45.560
Professor Thaler has been
awarded numerous honors

00:03:45.560 --> 00:03:47.360
for his extensive and illuminating work

00:03:47.360 --> 00:03:49.230
in behavioral economics.

00:03:49.230 --> 00:03:52.107
He is a member of the American
Academy of Arts and Sciences

00:03:52.107 --> 00:03:54.648
and in 2009, he was elected a fellow

00:03:54.648 --> 00:03:57.539
of the American Finance Association.

00:03:57.539 --> 00:03:59.760
And currently serves as vice president

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:02.510
of the American Economics Association.

00:04:02.510 --> 00:04:05.616
Please join me in welcoming
Professor Richard Thaler.

00:04:05.616 --> 00:04:08.033
